  "prompt": "How can I report someone on Quora?",
  "response": "Reporting someone on Quora depends on what they've done. Here's a breakdown of how to report different types of violations:\n\n**1. Reporting a Question:**\n\n*   **Navigate to the question:** Go to the question you want to report.\n*   **Click the three dots:** Look for the three vertical dots (ellipsis) near the question title. This is usually found on the right-hand side.\n*   **Select \"Report\":** Choose the \"Report\" option from the dropdown menu.\n*   **Choose a reason:** Select the most appropriate reason for reporting the question from the list provided (e.g., spam, inappropriate, hateful, misleading, off-topic, low-quality, duplicate).\n*   **Provide additional details (optional):** In some cases, you might be able to add further information to explain your report. This can be helpful if the reason isn't immediately obvious.\n*   **Submit:** Click the \"Submit\" or \"Report\" button to send your report.\n\n**2. Reporting an Answer:**\n\n*   **Navigate to the answer:** Go to the answer you want to report.\n*   **Click the three dots:** Look for the three vertical dots (ellipsis) near the bottom of the answer, often next to the \"Upvote,\" \"Downvote,\" and \"Comment\" options.\n*   **Select \"Report\":** Choose the \"Report\" option from the dropdown menu.\n*   **Choose a reason:** Select the most appropriate reason for reporting the answer from the list provided (e.g., spam, inappropriate, hateful, misleading, off-topic, low-quality, plagiarism, copyright violation).\n*   **Provide additional details (optional):** Explain your reason for reporting the answer in the text box. Be specific and clear. If it's plagiarism, include links to the original source.\n*   **Submit:** Click the \"Submit\" or \"Report\" button to send your report.\n\n**3. Reporting a Comment:**\n\n*   **Navigate to the comment:** Find the comment you want to report.\n*   **Click the three dots:** Look for the three vertical dots (ellipsis) near the comment.\n*   **Select \"Report\":** Choose the \"Report\" option from the dropdown menu.\n*   **Choose a reason:** Select the most appropriate reason for reporting the comment.\n*   **Provide additional details (optional):** Explain your reason.\n*   **Submit:** Click the \"Submit\" or \"Report\" button.\n\n**4. Reporting a Profile:**\n\n*   **Navigate to the profile:** Go to the profile page of the person you want to report.\n*   **Click the three dots:** Look for the three vertical dots (ellipsis) near the top of their profile, usually on the right-hand side.  It might be located next to the \"Follow\" button.\n*   **Select \"Report\":** Choose the \"Report\" option from the dropdown menu.\n*   **Choose a reason:** Select the most appropriate reason for reporting the profile (e.g., impersonation, spam, harassment, hateful content, other).\n*   **Provide additional details (optional):** Explain your reason in detail.  This is especially important when reporting a profile, as it helps Quora understand the context.  Include specific examples of the violations you've observed.\n*   **Submit:** Click the \"Submit\" or \"Report\" button.\n\n**5. Reporting a Space:**\n\n*   **Navigate to the Space:** Go to the Space you want to report.\n*   **Click the three dots:** Look for the three dots in the upper-right corner of the space page.\n*   **Select \"Report Space\":** Choose the \"Report Space\" option from the dropdown menu.\n*   **Choose a reason:** Select the most appropriate reason for reporting the space.\n*   **Provide additional details (optional):** Provide additional information that explains your decision.\n*   **Submit:** Click the \"Submit\" or \"Report\" button.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Be specific:** Provide as much detail as possible when explaining why you are reporting something. This helps Quora moderators understand the issue and take appropriate action.\n*   **Be respectful:** Even when reporting, maintain a respectful tone. Avoid personal attacks or inflammatory language.\n*   **Don't abuse the reporting system:** Only report content that genuinely violates Quora's policies.  False or frivolous reports can be counterproductive.\n*   **Quora's policies:** Familiarize yourself with Quora's Be Nice, Be Respectful policy and other guidelines to understand what types of content are prohibited.  This will help you make informed reporting decisions.  You can find these guidelines in Quora's Help Center.\n*   **Anonymity:** While your report is generally anonymous to the user you're reporting, Quora may need to share information with law enforcement if required by law.\n*   **Wait for review:** After submitting your report, Quora moderators will review it and take action if necessary. This process may take some time. You won't necessarily receive an immediate confirmation or update on the outcome.\n*   **Blocking:** If you're experiencing personal harassment, consider blocking the user in addition to reporting them. Blocking prevents them from interacting with you on Quora. You can do this from their profile page.\n\nBy following these steps and providing clear information, you can help Quora maintain a safe and productive environment for everyone.\n",
